cells.value: Looking to buy in Lexington.....Spoke with Charlotte Daily wife of David Daily owner of 3465 Covered   Wagon Trail and she said they are selling this house next May.They   want to retire in the country next year but is haviong problems   looking for a property that is 5-10 acres of land with a   pond/electricity/fence for their 2 horses.They have tried looking   for this kind of property in Manor,Elgin,Smithsville and Kyle but   didnt have any luck.She doesnt have price range in mind but when I called David he said that they will sell it for 160k because he saw some neighbors sell their house for this price.She added that   this house needs new carpets,New linolium for the masters bathroom   and exterior paint.Charlotte said that they can sell this house   rightaway if we have a buyer because they have a lot of relatives   who owns houses in the area and if they will be able to sell this   house they will just live in any of those houses with their   relatives.She also provided her email as  ***chardaily@yahoo.com   waiting for our email and resume.  PRE-QUALIFYING THE LISTING PRESENTATION  Before we come out there are a number of questions I need to ask youok?  1.	If what I say makes senseand you feel comfortable and confident that I cansell your homeare you planning to list your home with me when I come out on __________?***October 18 2014  2.	Are you planning to interview more than one agent for the job of selling your home? NO a.	Have you already established those appointments?*** NA b.	Yes? Great! When is your 1st appointment?*** NA c.	Will you interview all agents before you decide?*** NO i.	If no-we want to be the 2nd ii.	If yes (without ANY hesitation)- we want to be the last 3.	Tell me againwhere are you moving to? ***Anywhre in the Country  Bastrop, Manor, Elgin, Smithsville 4.	How soon do you need to be there?*** May next year,But will sell if we have a buyer 5.	If we sell you home in the next 30 days will that be a problem for you? ***They are having a garage sale in the next 2 weeks so after that they need about 30 days more 6.	What would happen if your home did not sell?*** Stay in the house until they successfully sell it. 7.	When we see youhow much do you want to list your home for? ***160k a.	As a professional real estate agent, we study homes and prices everyday, therefore I assume youll list with meat a price that will cause your home to sellcorrect? 8.	What is an acceptable selling price for you?***160k 9.	How much do you owe on the property? ***127k a.	If they hesitate-I understand your hesitation and the reason I want to know is to be able to prepare you a net sheet showing you what the sell of the home will financially yield you. (if this sells them make sure the listing agent knows they anticipate this sheet) 10.	Have you ever though about selling it yourself? (Ask in a confused tone as if this is the worst idea you have ever heard)***NO 11.	Will you help finance the home for a buyeror do you want your cash out? ***NA 12.	Are you current on your house payments? ***YES 13.	Are you going toPURCHASE ANOTHER HOME? *** YES  14.	In a minute or two would you please describe your house for me?*** Good condition, Corner lot, More space, Bigger than properties in the area, greenbelt 15.	How would you rate your house on a scale form 1 to 10? ***9 16.	What would make it a 10? Minor repairs, New carpets needed , Paint 17.	Do you have any questions before I arrive? ***NO 18.	Ive only spoken to you. Are there any other decisions makers I should speak with before I come over on October 18 2014? ***NONE a.	Will you be consulting anyone else before you hire an agent? 19.	Will all the decision makers be there when I arrive? 20.	So you knowour meeting should only take 30 minutesis that okay?  Fantastic! I look forward to hearing how your meeting with Katie Thornell goes on October 18 2014

cells.value: Name: Cynthia S Morgan Email: unusualoccasioncards@yahoo.com Contact: 512-329-5265 Motivation: Downsize/ thinking of her age Price Range: not aware If Moving (Place): Same area Address: 1405 Ridgecrest Dr Austin TX 78746  Additional Info:  She is thinking of selling it but she cant give a ball part figure   because its a hard property to determine a price for. Its a   really unique property. She went from a 5 person to a single   person living and the property has a separate building for her   office and a lot of space for storage. She is very much   interested in knowing the market value of her home right   now. The property was built in 1972. She put a brand new   commercial roof, its a flat roof house, its has custom gutters,   it has an unusual architecture behind the wall because it was   built by an opera singer to emulate the sound set up, had a lot   of remodeling done, floors are all marble except for 2 rooms   at the back and upgraded kitchen. The house is like a   sanctuary for her and she thinks that it might be hard for her   to find another property similar to her home when she   downsize. She is actually looking for a small piece of   property or land where she can build a small modern house.   The plan is to put it on the market next year because she is   thinking about her age, the size of the house and she knows   that the market is so strong right now. She wants to have   someone from our team help her come up with a price point   that would help her decide. She said that her schedule is   clear on the first week of october and would like to have   someone from our team come by to her place and have a   discussion. We are the first team to contact her and this is   gonna be her first consultation with a listing agent. She is   going to be the only one deciding when we come to her place   on october 3rd Friday. It would be better if we can also have a   buyers agent come by to help her look for a new property.

cells.value: PRE-QUALIFYING THE LISTING PRESENTATION  Before we come out there are a number of questions I need to ask youok? 1.	If what I say makes senseand you feel comfortable and confident that I cansell your homeare you planning to list your home with me when I come out on __________? ***11/07/2014 11am-12pm 2.	Are you planning to interview more than one agent for the job of selling your home? ***NO a.	Have you already established those appointments? b.	Yes? Great! When is your 1st appointment? c.	Will you interview all agents before you decide? i.	If no-we want to be the 2nd ii.	If yes (without ANY hesitation)- we want to be the last 3.	Tell me againwhere are you moving to? ****Near San Marcos (somewhere in the Country) 4.	How soon do you need to be there?  ***As soon as he sells this property 5.	If we sell you home in the next 30 days will that be a problem for you? ***NO 6.	What would happen if your home did not sell? ***Have it rented 7.	When I see youhow much do you want to list your home for? ***350k a.	As a professional real estate agent, we study homes and prices everyday, therefore I assume youll list with meat a price that will cause you home to sellcorrect? ***YES 8.	What is an acceptable selling price for you? ***350k 9.	How much do you owe on the property? ***NONE a.	If they hesitate-I understand your hesitation and the reason I want to know is to be able to prepare you a net sheet showing you what the sell of the home will financially yield you. (if this sells them make sure the listing agent knows they anticipate this sheet) 10.	Have you ever though about selling it yourself? (Ask in a confused tone as if this is the worst idea you have ever heard)  ***YES 11.	Will you help finance the home for a buyeror do you want your cash out? 12.	Are you current on your house payments? *** NA 13.	Are you going toPURCHASE ANOTHER HOME? *** YES 14.	In a minute or two would you please describe your house for me? ***Very accessible,updated,perfect house to start a family 15.	How would you rate your house on a scale form 1 to 10?  ***10 16.	What would make it a 10?  ***NONE 17.	Do you have any questions before I arrive?  ***NONE 18.	Ive only spoken to you. Are there any other decisions makers I should speak with before I come over on_______?  ***NONE a.	Will you be consulting anyone else before you hire an agent? ***NO 19.	Will all the decision makers be there when I arrive?  ***YES 20.	So you knowour meeting should only take 30 minutesis that okay? ***YES  Fantastic! I look forward to hearing how your meeting with Katie Thornel goes on 11/07/2014
